user.about:
Based in Adelaide, South Australia, we try our best to venture near and far to witness the best show on earth : light!

We hope that the images in our stream convey the prevailing mood at the time we photographed the scene to capture the raw essence of the scene (forgive the pun). The processing we do is aimed at reliving that moment in more than just a visual sense and is achieved through considered post processing.

Bio:iiic
Self-taught in Photography, Jessica has had her work published Internationally in magazines, books and with entertainment clients including Lucas Arts. Jessica has a Bachelor's Degree in Fine Art (Painting), and has worked for video game companies such as Blizzard Entertainment. A professional photographer for five years, she has won numerous awards, including the 2013 Emerging Professional Fine Art Photographer from Digital Photo Pro Magazine. Her projects range from documenting a scoring session for the film, "Red Tails" in Prague to creating book cover art worldwide. Her work has been featured in issues of such magazines as Digital Photo Pro, Wedding Nouveau, and Practical Photography magazines. She shoots with a Canon 5D Mark III, and specializes in capturing and retouching portraits with natural light using her own presets, actions, overlays and textures.

“You drown not by falling into a river, but by staying submerged in it.”
Paulo Coelho
A gorgeous hike give access to this wonderful golden canyon with waters rich in tannic acids, and at the very end this quite photogenic and peaceful waterfall. This beauty is hidden in plain sight in the highlands of Brazil… From the old archives, as I travel vicariously through my photographs. Thank you for stopping by!

user.about:
Welcome to my portfolio!
Above all, I love to explore the outdoors. Photography has pushed me to go places I otherwise would never think of going to. Since taking photography seriously, I have backpacked and hiked to incredible places, met great people and enjoyed nature like never before. 
My love for photography took off dramatically when was I given a digital SLR camera, which has allowed me to bring me to print all the colors, textures, drama, and beautiful scenes that I was seeing. I love to use filters, and I do a fairly large amount long exposure photography so I can capture one element that conventional photography does not: time moving.

I was born and grew up in Minas Gerais – Brazil, which is where my love for photography began, but I have been living in the US for over 18 years now. As a child, my dad and I would take pictures on vacation with his simple point and shoot Kodak camera. Back then that is all we had-equipment and film was too expensive, but we made the best of it, and so my passion began. Photography is my escape, it takes me to incredible places, and is where I can express some of my creativity. When the D-SLR revolution happened, I was able to justify the investment and never looked back. However, in my full-time day job I work as a Systems Engineer for a biomedical company.

My name is Lavan. I’m a bird photographer, I’ve been photographing for almost 13 years. I specialize in making wildlife and natural resources, habitats photography. Truth is stranger than fiction, and I’ve always been compelled by that fact, especially here in many Places Right now I’m really passionate about my work and of course, there will always be those who look only at technique, who ask `how’, while others of a more curious nature will ask `why’. Personally, I’ve always preferred inspiration to information.

photos.description:
Here’s a fairly old image I made in Mt. Rainier National Park many years ago, looking south towards the small Tatoosh Range on an autumn evening. “Tatoosh” was a word in the local native language that roughly translates into “nourishing breast.” I’m not sure if that has had a subliminal influence on why I love coming back to this place often. 😳

You can learn how I create my images at www.ryandyar.com 👍👍 Thank you for taking a look at this photo.
